============================================================
  FAMOUS PEOPLE
============================================================

Name:          Ada Lovelace
Lived:         1815 - 1852
Nationality:   English
Field:         Computing
Known For:     First computer algorithm
Contribution:  Wrote first algorithm for Babbage's machine; recognized computing potential
Quote:         "The Analytical Engine weaves algebraic patterns."

Name:          Alan Turing
Lived:         1912 - 1954
Nationality:   English
Field:         Computing
Known For:     Turing machine, codebreaking
Contribution:  Father of computer science; broke Enigma; Turing test for AI
Quote:         "We can only see a short distance ahead, but we can see plenty there that needs to be done."

Name:          Stephen Hawking
Lived:         1942 - 2018
Nationality:   English
Field:         Physics
Known For:     Black hole radiation
Contribution:  Proved black holes emit radiation; A Brief History of Time; communicated science publicly
Quote:         "Intelligence is the ability to adapt to change."

============================================================
  DISEASES & MEDICINE
============================================================

Disease:     Diabetes Type 2
Type:        Metabolic
Pathogen:    Non-communicable
Transmission:Lifestyle
Symptoms:    Thirst, frequent urination, fatigue
Treatment:   Metformin, lifestyle, insulin
Deaths/yr:   1.5M
Vaccine:     No
Discovered:  1922

Disease:     Cholera
Type:        Bacterial
Pathogen:    Vibrio cholerae
Transmission:Contaminated water
Symptoms:    Profuse watery diarrhea, vomiting
Treatment:   Oral rehydration, antibiotics
Deaths/yr:   0.095M
Vaccine:     Yes
Discovered:  1854

Disease:     Ebola
Type:        Viral
Pathogen:    Ebola virus
Transmission:Bodily fluids contact
Symptoms:    Fever, bleeding, organ failure
Treatment:   Monoclonal antibodies, supportive
Deaths/yr:   0.001M
Vaccine:     Yes (Ervebo for Zaire strain)
Discovered:  1976

